        "descriptions": [
          {
            "description": "This data set contains Raw data in .FIT format taken \n by New Horizons Multispectral Visible Imaging Camera \n instrument during the JUPITER ENCOUNTER mission phase. \n \n These data were migrated from the PDS3 dataset: \n NH-J-MVIC-2-JUPITER-V2.0.\n \n The Ralph (LEISA and MVIC) Jupiter activities included calibration \n observations using Callisto and Jupiter as a target, scientific \n observations of Jovian targets, opnav test observations of \n Callisto, and mapping of solar input aperture. \n \n This version includes data downlinked from 01/11/2007 through 06/27/2007.\n \n Labels were redesigned during migration using the .FIT header and PDS3 .LBL\n files, but the data files are unchanged from their PDS3 version.",
            "descriptionType": "Abstract"
          }
        ],
